{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "07", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "22", "M": "52", "S": "29"}}, "news": [{"title": "Finish probe, speed up trial in illegal sand mining case: Madras HC", "para": "Madras High Court has directed authorities to finalize a pending inquiry against officials involved in illegal sand mining. The court also urged CB-CID to expedite the trial. This case concerns the unlawful excavation and transport of sand from the Thamirabarani river to Kerala. An assistant engineer was suspended for allegedly approving farm ponds used for illegal operations.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/allied-industries/madras-hc-urges-quick-action-in-illegal-sand-mining-case/131570803?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-165928/131570803.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "allied-industries"}, {"title": "Lucknow: Government bans land sale within LDA housing projects on Sultanpur Road", "para": "The Uttar Pradesh government has banned land transactions in the proposed IT City and Wellness City areas of Lucknow. This move aims to stop speculative deals and ensure that only original landowners benefit from the land pooling scheme. The prohibition is effective immediately. Landowners recorded in revenue records will be eligible for developed plots.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/lucknow-bans-land-sales-in-lda-housing-projects-a-move-to-protect-local-landowners/131570766?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-27328/131570766.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Ghaziabad to start eviction drive in illegal colonies along Hindon", "para": "Ghaziabad authorities are launching a coordinated drive to remove encroachments along the Hindon river, following a state report to the National Green Tribunal highlighting 258 unauthorized colonies discharging untreated sewage. District Magistrate Ravindra Kumar Mandar stressed the need to identify illegal occupations by cross-referencing records and ground conditions, emphasizing zero tolerance for riverbank constructions to prevent floods and ecological damage.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/ghaziabad-launches-major-drive-to-evict-illegal-colonies-along-hindon-river/131570600?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-141450/131570600.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}]}